          A   prolonged   timing  of  millisecond  pulsars  has  revealed
          low-frequency  uncorrelated  noise, presumably of astrophysical
          origin,  in  the pulse arrival time (PAT) residuals for some of
          them.  In  most  cases,  pulsars  in  globular  clusters show a
          low-frequency  modulation  of  their  rotational phase and spin
