astro-ph/0601004 [abs, ps, pdf, other] :
          Title: Relic keV sterile neutrinos and reionization
          Authors: Peter L. Biermann, Alexander Kusenko
          Comments: 4 pages, 2 figures
          A  sterile  neutrino  with  mass of several keV can account for
          cosmological  dark  matter,  as  well  as  explain the observed
          velocities  of  pulsars.  We  show  that X-rays produced by the
          decays   of   these  relic  sterile  neutrinos  can  boost  the
          production  of  molecular  hydrogen,  which  can  speed  up the
          cooling  of  gas  and  the  early star formation, which can, in
          turn,  lead  to a reionization of the universe at a high enough
          redshift to be consistent with the WMAP results.


   
