          light-curve and radial velocity solution we find the masses and
          radii  of  the two components to be 30 +/- 1 and 16 +/- 1 solar
          masses  and  7.5  +/-  0.5  and  5.3 +/- 0.5 solar radii. These
          radii,  and hence also the luminosities, are smaller than those
          of  normal  O-type  stars,  but  similar  to recently born ZAMS
