          spectra  obtained  with  the  Advanced CCD Imaging Spectrometer
          aboard  the  Chandra  X-ray  Observatory.  The  dominant  X-ray
          feature  of  the  30 Doradus nebula is the intricate network of
          diffuse  emission  generated  by  interacting stellar winds and
          supernovae  working together to create vast superbubbles filled
          with  hot  plasma.  We  construct  maps  of  the region showing
          variations  in  plasma  temperature (T = 3--9 million degrees),
