          Comments: Accepted for publication in PRE
          Subj-class: Statistical Mechanics
          A   proof   of   the   relativistic  $H$-theorem  by  including
          nonextensive   effects   is   given.   As  it  happens  in  the
          nonrelativistic  limit, the molecular chaos hypothesis advanced
          by  Boltzmann  does  not  remain  valid,  and the second law of
          thermodynamics  combined  with a duality transformation implies
          that  the  q-parameter  lies  on the interval [0,2]. It is also
          proved  that  the  collisional equilibrium states (null entropy
          source  term)  are  described by the relativistic $q$-power law
          extension   of   the  exponential  Juttner  distribution  which
          reduces,  in  the  nonrelativistic domain, to the Tsallis power
          law  function.  As a simple illustration of the basic approach,
          we    derive    the   relativistic   nonextensive   equilibrium
          distribution  for  a  dilute charged gas under the action of an
          electromagnetic  field  $F^{{\mu\nu}}$.  Such results reduce to
          the  standard ones in the extensive limit, thereby showing that
          the  nonextensive entropic framework can be harmonized with the
          space-time ideas contained in the special relativity theory.


