          to  the  quark  phase ($\rho_0=2.5\times10^{14}$g/cm$^3$ is the
          saturation  density  of  nuclear  matter), we find that neutron
          stars  lighter  than  $1.5M_{\odot}$  cannot reach a deconfined
          phase.  Depending  on  the  EOS,  neutron  stars  of  more than
          $1.5M_{\odot}$  can  enter  a  quark  phase  only  if  they are
          spinning  faster  than  about  3  milliseconds as observed now,
