          explained,  in  this  framework,  by  the  primary  spin  being
          slightly faster than the orbital motion ($\alpha <or= 1.1$). In
          this  case, the associated spin-orbit coupling transfers to the
          orbit  a significant amount of angular momentum, thus partially
          balancing  that  lost  to  GW emission. All expectations can be
          tested  in  the  near  future  to  confirm the viability of the
          model.


   
