          synthetically,   considering  the  influence  of  {\it  r-}mode
          instability. Our results show that the cooling of strange stars
          with non-ultra strong magnetic fields is delayed by the heating
          due  to  the  {\it r-}modes damping during million years, while
          the  spin-down  of  the  stars  is  dominated  by gravitational
          radiation.  Especially  for  the  strange  stars  in a possible
