          emissivity,  and  the specific heat involving paring quarks are
          blocked. It leads to the cooling of these color superconducting
          stars  is  very slow, and the stars can remain high temperature
          within   million   years  differing  completely  from  previous
          understanding.  In  this  case,  a strange star in color-flavor
          locked  phase  can be located at the bottom of its {\it r-}mode
          instability window for a long time, but does not spin down to a
