          astronomical  sources being binary super-massive black holes in
          galaxy  cores.  The Parkes Pulsar Timing Array project uses the
          Parkes   64-m   radio   telescope   to  make  precision  timing
          observations of a sample of about 20 millisecond pulsars with a
