          to  produce  significant  numbers  of black-hole low-mass X-ray
          binaries.  However,  by simply reducing the mass-loss rate from
          helium  stars  adopted  in  the  standard model, to a rate that
          agrees  with  the  latest  data, we produce a good match to the
          observations.  Including  low-mass  X-ray  binaries that evolve
          from   intermediate-mass   systems  also  leads  to  favourable
          results.  We  stress  that  constraints  on  the  X-ray  binary
          population  provided  by observations are used here merely as a
