          effects   in   the  plasma  of  pulsar  magnetosphere.  Induced
          scattering  of  radio waves by the plasma particles is found to
          lead  to  an  efficient redistribution of the radio emission in
          frequency.   With  the  steep  spectrum  of  pulsar  radiation,
          intensity  transfer  between  the widely spaced frequencies may
          imply  significant  narrow-band amplification of the radiation.
