astro-ph/0605380 [abs, ps, pdf, other] :
          Title:  A  strong $\ddot{\nu} - \dot{\nu}$ correlation in radio
          pulsars with implications for torque variations
          Authors: J. O. Urama, B. Link, J. M. Weisberg
          Comments: MNRAS, in press. 5 pages, 2 figures
          We  present  an  analysis  of  the spin-down parameters for 131
          radio  pulsars  for  which $\ddot\nu$ has been well determined.
          These  pulsars  have characteristic ages ranging from $10^{3} -
          10^{8}$  yr  and  spin  periods  in the range 0.4--30 s; nearly
          equal  numbers of pulsars have $\ddot\nu>0$ as $\ddot\nu<0$. We
          find  a strong correlation of $\ddot\nu$ with $\dot{\nu}$, {\em
          independent  of  the  sign of} $\ddot\nu$. We suggest that this
