          total  number  of  planetary  nebulae  (PN)  in the Galaxy that
          descend  from  single  stars and stars in binary systems. Using
          the  most  recent  literature  results  on galactic and stellar
          formation  as  well  as stellar evolution, we predict the total
          number  of  galactic  PNe  with radii <0.9 pc to be (46,000 +/-
          13,000).  We  do  not claim this to be the complete population,
