          PN  birthrate  density  estimates  of  2.1 x 10^{-12} PN/yr per
          cubic  pc,  which  are  based  on  local  PN  counts and the PN
          distance scale, but more in line with the white dwarf birthrate
          densities  determined  by  Liebert  et  al.  ((1.0  +/- 0.25) x
          10^{-12}  WD/yr  per  cubic  pc).  The  predicted  PN birthrate
          density  will  be revised down, if we assume that only binaries
          make  PNe.  This revision will imply that the PN distance scale
          has to be revised to larger values.


   
