          for  nu_R  emission, and mu_nu < (0.4 - 0.6) 10^{-12} mu_B from
          the  limit  on the averaged time of the neutrino spin-flip. The
          best  astrophysical upper bound on the neutrino magnetic moment
          is improved by the factor of 3 to 7.


   
