          disks also can be formed around neutron stars which were formed
          during  collapse of accreting oxygen-neon white dwarfs. We have
          estimated  frequencies  of  events  which  lead to a rotational
          collapse   concerned   with   formation   of  rapidly  rotating
          relativistic  objects  in  the Galaxy. We made our calculations
          using the "Scenario Machine".


   
