          Authors: O. E. Nicotra
          Comments: 5 pages, 3 figures, 1 table
          To  investigate  the stability of the protoneutron stars in its
          early   evolution,  the  minimum  gravitational  mass  plays  a
          fundamental   role.  This  quantity  depends  upon  temperature
          profile   assumed.  We  study  within  a  static  approach  the
          stability  of  a protoneutron star. In particular we focus on a
          suitable    temperature    profile   suggested   by   dynamical
          calculations.   We  indeed  consider  a  protoneutron  star  as
          composed by an isothermal core and an isentropic outer part. To
