          nonthermal  emission  detected  from  X-ray  nebulae powered by
          millisecond  pulsars,  as  well as from pulsar winds shocked in
          binary  systems  with  millisecond pulsars as companions. These
          and   other   most   important   results  obtained  from  X-ray
          observations of millisecond pulsars are reviewed in this paper,
