          Title:  Incompatibility  of long-period neutron star precession
          with creeping neutron vortices
          Authors: Bennett Link
          Comments: 4 pages
          Aims:  To  determine whether ``vortex creep'' in neutron stars,
          the  slow  motion  of  neutron vortices with respect to pinning
          sites   in   the  core  or  inner  crust,  is  consistent  with
          observations  of  long-period  precession.  Methods:  Using the
          concept  of vortex drag, I discuss the precession dynamics of a
          star  with  imperfectly-pinned  (i.e.,  "creeping'')  vortices.
