          Authors: D. Vanbeveren, E. De Donder
          Comments: 15 pages, 9 figures, accepted for New Astronomy
          Low metallicity very massive stars with an initial mass between
          140  Mo  and  260  Mo  can be subdivided into two groups: those
          between  140  Mo  and  200  Mo which produce a relatively small
          amount  of  Fe, and those with a mass between 200 Mo and 260 Mo
          where  the  Fe-yield  ejected during the supernova explosion is
