          starquakes  that  twist the external magnetic field of the star
          and  induce electric currents in the closed magnetosphere. Once
          twisted,  the  magnetosphere cannot untwist immediately because
          of  its self-induction. The self-induction electric field lifts
          particles  from  the  stellar  surface,  accelerates  them, and
          initiates avalanches of pair creation in the magnetosphere. The
