          interpret  the  recent observations of early afterglows of long
          Gamma-Ray  Bursts  (GRB)  with  the  Swift satellite. This is a
          three-stage   model  within  the  context  of  a  core-collapse
          supernova.  Stage  1  is  an  accreting  (proto-)  neutron star
