          publication in Science
          Journal-ref: Science, Volume 313, Issue 5788, pp. 812-814
          (2006)
          We report high-angular-resolution measurements of polarized
          dust emission toward the low-mass protostellar system NGC 1333
          IRAS 4A. We show that in this system the observed magnetic
          field morphology is in agreement with the standard theoretical
          models of the formation of Sun-like stars in magnetized
          molecular clouds at scales of a few hundred astronomical units;
          gravity has overcome magnetic support, and the magnetic field
          traces a clear hourglass shape. The magnetic field is
          substantially more important than turbulence in the evolution
