          neutrinos can simultaneously explain the cosmological dark
          matter and the observed velocities of pulsars. To satisfy all
          cosmological bounds, the relic sterile neutrinos must be
          produced sufficiently cold. This is possible in a class of
          models with a gauge-singlet Higgs boson, coupled to the
          neutrinos as a singlet Majoron. Sterile dark matter can be
