          surface of a rapidly-rotating neutron star in order to
          construct light curves for X-ray pulsars and bursters. These
          calculations are for realistic models of rapidly-rotating
          neutron stars which take into account both the correct exterior
          metric and the oblate shape of the star. We find that the most
