          Barcelona July 2006
          Observations of the inner radian of the Galactic disk at very
          high energy (VHE) gamma-rays have revealed at least 16 new
          sources. Besides shell type super-nova remnants, pulsar wind
          nebulae (PWN) appear to be a dominant source population in the
          catalogue of VHE gamma-ray sources. Except for the Crab nebula,
          the newly discovered PWN are resolved at VHE gamma-rays to be
          spatially extended (5-20 pc). Currently, at least 3 middle aged
          ($t>10$ kyrs) PWN (Vela X, G18.0-0.7, and G313.3+0.6 in the
