          Polaris field. Two distant companions C and D are not X-rays
          sources and hence are not young enough to be physical
          companions of the Cepheid. There is one additional stellar
          X-ray source in the field, located $253''$ from Polaris A,
          which is a possible companion. Further investigation of such a
          distant companion is valuable to confirm the full extent of the
          system.


   
