          Aims. This study aims to determine the level and constancy of
          the Spite plateau as definitively as possible from homogeneous
          high-quality VLT-UVES spectra of 19 of the most metal-poor
          dwarf stars known. Methods. Our high-resolution (R ~ 43000),
          high S/N spectra are analysed with OSMARCS 1D LTE model
          atmospheres and turbospectrum synthetic spectra to determine
          effective temperatures, surface gravities, and metallicities as
          well as Li abundances for our stars. Results. Eliminating a
          cool subgiant and a spectroscopic binary, we find 8 stars to
          have -3.5 < [Fe/H] < -3.0 and 9 stars with -3.0 < [Fe/H] <
