          comparable to the observed cooling-age difference and show that
          this puts a strong constraint on the model solutions. However,
          the scenario in which the primary loses its envelope in an
          isotropic wind and the secondary transfers its envelope, which
          is then re-emitted isotropically, can explain the observed age
          differences as well. One of these solutions explains the
          DB-nature of the oldest white dwarf in PG1115+116 along the
          evolutionary scenario proposed by Maxted et al. (2002a), in
