          Title: Computing Limb Darkening Coefficients from Stellar
          Atmosphere Models
          Authors: David Heyrovsky
          Comments: 22 pages, 6 figures; accepted by The Astrophysical
          Journal
          We explore the sensitivity of limb darkening coefficients
          computed from stellar atmosphere models to different
          least-squares fitting methods. We demonstrate that conventional
          methods are strongly biased to fitting the stellar limb. Our
          suggested method of fitting by minimizing the radially
          integrated squared residual yields improved fits with better
          flux conservation. The differences of the obtained coefficients
          from commonly used values are observationally significant. We
          show that the new values are in better agreement with solar
          limb darkening measurements as well as with coefficients
          reported from analyses of eclipsing binary light curves.


   
