          emission in the binary merger of equal-mass black holes as
          obtained from numerical relativity simulations. Results from
          the evolution of three sets of initial data are explored in
          detail, corresponding to different initial separations of the
          black holes. We find that to a good approximation the inspiral
          phase of the evolution is quasi-circular, followed by a
          "blurred, quasi-circular plunge", then merger and ring down. We
