          with surface values of specific angular momentum j = 2-15
          j_sun. All high specific angular momentum systems with j =
          20-30 j_sun are confined to the primary stars of binaries. This
          provides novel empirical evidence for rotational disk locking
          and again demonstrates the much shorter disk lifetimes in close
          binary systems compared to single star systems. We estimate the
          characteristic mean disk dissipation timescale to be ~5 Myr and
