          stars to galaxies - across the range of masses"
          We examine the possibility that Ultraluminous X-ray sources
          (ULXs) represent the extreme end of the black hole X-ray binary
          (XRB) population. Based on their X-ray properties, we suggest
          that ULXs are persistently in a high/hard spectral state and we
          propose a new disk-jet model that can accomodate both a high
          accretion rate and a hard X-ray spectrum. Our model predicts
          that the modified disk emission can be substantially softer
