          3-10 MeV depending on the strength of the shear motion at the
          collision interface between the NSs and thus depending on the
          initial NS spins. About 10^{-3}-10^{-2} M_sun of NS matter
          become gravitationally unbound during or right after the
          merging process. This matter consists of a hot/high-entropy
          component from the collision interface and (only in case of
          asymmetric systems) of a cool/low-entropy component from the
          spiral arm tips. (abridged)


   
