          Rossi-XTE on two microquasars: the persistent high-mass system
          Cygnus X-1 and the transient low-mass binary SWIFT
          J1753.5-0127. INTEGRAL observed Cygnus X-1 from 2002 to 2004:
          the spectral (5-1000 keV) properties of the source, seen at
          least in three distinct spectral states, show disc and corona
          changes. In 2003 June, a high-energy tail at several hundred
          keV in excess of the thermal Comptonization model was observed,
