          Authors: W. Bednarek
          Comments: 5 pages, 4 figures, A&A accepted
          TeV gamma-ray emission from two massive binaries of the
          microquasar type, LS 5039 and LS I +61$^{\rm o}$ 303, show
          clear variability with their orbital periods. Our purpose is to
          calculate the GeV and TeV $\gamma$-ray light curves from the
          massive binary LS 5039 which are expected in the specific
          Inverse Compton $e^\pm$ pair cascade model. This model
          successfully predicted the basic features of the high energy
          $\gamma$-ray emission from LS 5039 and LS I +61 303. In the
          calculations we apply the Monte Carlo code which follows the IC
