          scenario is not necessary. Furthermore, I show that the
          scenario in which the neutron star in 2S 0114+650 is assumed to
          be a magnetar descendant encounters major difficulties in
          explaining the evolution of the massive companion. An
          alternative interpretation of the spin evolution of the neutron
          star in this system is presented and the problem raised by
          association of the 10000 s pulsations with the spin period of
          the neutron star is briefly discussed.


   
