          for the binary pulsar PSR J1811-1736. One post-Keplerian
          parameter, the relativistic periastron advance, is measured and
          leads to the determination of the total mass of this binary
          system. The pulse profile at 1.4 GHz is heavily broadened by
          interstellar scattering, limiting the timing precision
          achievable at this frequency and the measurability of other
          post-keplerian parameters. Interstellar scattering is unlikely
