          investigate the possible $\gamma$-ray emission features from
          another compact massive binary of the microquasar type, Cyg
          X-1. We conclude that the observational constraints at lower
          energies (from MeV to GeV) suggest that the spectrum of
          electrons injected in the jet is likely steeper than in other
          TeV $\gamma$-ray microquasars. The cascade $\gamma$-ray
