          conference "Isolated Neutron Stars: From the Interior to the
          Surface" eds. S. Zane, R. Turolla, D. Page; Astrophysics &
          Space Science in press
          The anomalous X-ray pulsar 4U 0142+61 was recently detected in
          the mid infrared bands with the SPITZER Observatory (Wang,
          Chakrabarty & Kaplan 2006). This observation is the first
          instance for a disk around an AXP. From a reanalysis of optical
          and infrared data, we show that the observations indicate that
          the disk is likely to be an active disk rather than a passive
          dust disk beyond the light cylinder, as proposed in the
