          in B and V filters are analysed and a distance of 8kpc is
          inferred. Three additional eclipsing binaries, which are
          probable late O or early B-type cluster members, are
          discovered, but none of the known early O-type stars in the
          cluster displays significant photometric variability above 1%
          at the 1-sigma level. The twelve brightest O-type stars are
          found to have spectral types between O3 and O6.5, significantly
          earlier than previously thought.
