          We present here the current status of pulsar simulations for
          the Large Area Telescope, the main instrument on the GLAST
          mission. We present "PulsarSpectrum", a pulsar simulator that
          can reproduce with high detail gamma-ray emission from pulsars.
          "PulsarSpectrum" takes into account advanced timing effects,
          e.g. period changes with time, barycentering effects and
          glitches. Other ancillary tools have been built to provide the
          simulator with a realistic population of pulsars and their
          ephemerides. All these tools are currently used in the GLAST
