          We present a systematic analysis of all the BeppoSAX data of
          SGR 1900+14. The observations spanning five years show that the
          source was brighter than usual on two occasions: ~20 days after
          the August 1998 giant flare and during the 10^5 sec long X-ray
          afterglow following the April 2001 intermediate flare. In the
          latter case, we explore the possibility of describing the
          observed short term softening only with a change of the
