          of 0.45 and hydrogen column density of 4\times10^{22} cm^{-2},
          both with large uncertainties due to the strong correlation
          between these parameters. A search for pulsations resulted in a
          106 s period candidate, which however has a low significance of
          97.9%. We found no infrared-optical counterparts for this
          source. The second brightest source, CXOU J180441.9-214224,
          which has been detected with Suzaku, is either extended or
          multiple, with the flux of about 10^{-13} ergs cm^{-2} s^{-1}.
