          associated with nearby stars. Although one or both of the two
          brighter X-ray sources could be faint accreting binaries or
          remote pulsars with pulsar wind nebulae (hence possible TeV
          sources), their relation to HESS J1804-216 remains elusive. The
          possibility that HESS J1804-216 is powered by the relativistic
          wind from the young pulsar B1800-21, located at a distance of
          about 10 pc from the TeV source, still remains a more plausible
          option.



