          We report the results of simultaneous observations of the Vela
          pulsar in X-rays and radio from the RXTE satellite and the
          Mount Pleasant Radio Observatory in Tasmania. We sought
          correlations between the Vela's X-ray and radio flux densities
          and radio arrival times on a pulse by pulse basis. We found
          significantly higher flux density in Vela's main X-ray peak
