          We present a detailed study of the single radio pulses of PSR
          B0656+14. The emission can be characterized by two separate
          populations of pulses: bright pulses have a narrow ``spiky''
          appearance in contrast to the underlying weaker broad pulses.
          The shape of the pulse profile requires an unusually long
          timescale to achieve stability (over 25,000 pulses at 327 MHz)
