          take place on the surface of accreting neutron stars. The wait
          time between consecutive bursts is set by the time required to
          accumulate the fuel needed to trigger a new burst; this is at
          least one hour. Sometimes secondary bursts are observed,
          approximately 10 min after the main burst. These short
          wait-time bursts are not yet understood. We observed the
          low-mass X-ray binary and X-ray burster EXO 0748-676 with
          XMM-Newton for 158 h, during 7 uninterrupted observations
          lasting up to 30 h each. We detect 76 X-ray bursts. Most
