          curve and propose a classification scheme for GRBs based on
          this behaviour. As found for previous smaller samples, the
          earliest X-ray light curve can be well described by an
          exponential which relaxes into a power law, often with flares
          superimposed. The later emission is well fit using a similar
          functional form and we find that these two functions provide a
          good description of the entire X-ray light curve. For the
