          gamma-ray emissions above the TeV originated from the hadronic
          scattering of cosmic rays (CR) with the interstellar medium
          (ISM). Differently from previous works, where a uniform CR
          density was assumed, we estimate the spatial distribution of
          primary nuclei by means of numerical simulations considering
          several models of the galactic magnetic field. Assuming that CR
          sources are supernova remnants (SNR), we use a distribution of
          those objects as estimated from observations of pulsars and
          progenitor stars.
