          beneath the burning layer. We then examine the impact of the
          beta-decay-limited ``hot'' CNO cycle on the stability of
          burning. Though this plays a significant role for accreting
          neutron stars, we find that for accreting white dwarfs, it can
          only increase the range of stably-burning accretion rates for
