          capability to simulate millisecond pulsars, which are old,
          recycled pulsars with extremely short periods. We model the
          spatial distribution of the simulated pulsars by assuming that
          they start with a random kick velocity and then evolve through
          the Galactic potential. We use a polar cap/slot gap model for
          $\gamma$-ray emission from both millisecond and ordinary
