          Title: Generation of Pulsar Radio Emission
          Authors: G. Gogoberidze, G.Z. Machabeli, V.V. Usov
          Comments: 10 pages, 1 figure, submitted to ApJ Letters
          We demonstrate that nonlinear decay of obliquely propagating
          Langmuir waves into another Langmuir and Alfven waves is
          possible in a one-dimensional, highly relativistic, streaming,
          pair plasma. Based on this we present a new mechanism of pulsar
          radio emission that involves development and quasilinear
          relaxation of two stream instability, induced scattering of
          generated Langmuir waves by plasma particles and nonlinear
          conversion of Langmuir waves into Alfven waves. It is shown
          that characteristic frequency of generated Alfven waves is much
          less than the plasma frequency and consistent with the
          observational data on pulsar radio emission.


   
