          only of kinematic information about different populations but
          does not make any assumptions about their respective mass
          functions, we find that the likelihood ratio is L_halo/L_SMC =
          20. Hence, halo lenses are strongly favored but SMC lenses are
          not definitively ruled out. Similar Spitzer observations of
          additional lenses toward the Magellanic Clouds would clarify
          the nature of the lens population. The Space Interferometry
          Mission could make even more constraining measurements.


   
