          Parkes multibeam survey was effective in detecting nulling
          pulsars. We have made 2-hour observations of 23 pulsars which
          showed evidence for pulse nulling or mode changing in the
          survey data. Because of the low flux density of these pulsars,
          in most cases averaging times of between 10 s and 60 s were
          necessary and so this analysis is insensitive to very short
          nulls. Seven of the pulsars had null fractions of more than 40%
