          telescope. Of these thirteen, five were found to be binary,
          with separations ranging from 0.04" to 0.6" and flux ratios
          from 1.4 to 3.7. In all cases, the companions are likely to be
          physically associated with the primaries (probability >
          4-sigma). Using the theoretical models of Baraffe et al.
